explanation.en:
This patient's thoracic aortic aneurysm repair has been complicated by ISCHEMIC INJURY to the ANTERIOR TWO-THIRDS of the spinal cord (SC). This area is perfused by the ANTERIOR SPINAL ARTERY, which receives blood flow from segmental arteries (eg, intercostal arteries) arising off the thoracic aorta. Disruption of circulation to this area classically results in ANTERIOR CORD SYNDROME, characterized by the following bilateral tract lesions and clinical signs:

* Spinothalamic tract (STT): LOSS of PAIN/TEMPERATURE (lateral spinothalamic) and CRUDE TOUCH (anterior spinothalamic) sensation 1-2 levels below the lesion.
* Anterior horn (lower motor neuron): flaccid paralysis and muscle atrophy at the level of the lesion.
* Lateral corticospinal tract (CST) (upper motor neuron): PARALYSIS below the level of the lesion. Flaccid paralysis from spinal shock (ie, temporary loss of all distal SC function) occurs initially, but upper motor neuron signs (eg, spasticity, hyperreflexia) subsequently develop over days to weeks.

As in this patient, the DORSAL COLUMNS are typically spared (due to intact circulation from the posterior spinal arteries), preserving proprioceptive, vibratory, and light touch sensation below the level of the lesion. {{exhibit_2}}

(Choice B) Complete loss of all lower extremity sensation (due to injury of the STTs and dorsal columns) and motor function (due to injury of the CSTs) may be seen in complete SC injury, as can occur in SC transection.

(Choices C and E) An isolated defect of crude touch sensation or pain/temperature sensation could occur only with isolated injury to the anterior or lateral STT, respectively. Because the anterior spinal artery also supplies the tracts (eg, CSTs) surrounding the STTs, it is extremely uncommon to have bilateral injury to only the anterior or lateral STT.

(Choice D) Diminished proprioception and motor function can occur with simultaneous injury to the dorsal columns and CSTs. A classic cause is subacute combined degeneration of the dorsal and lateral SC white matter, which is seen in VITAMIN B12 DEFICIENCY. {{exhibit_3}}

(Choice F) Selective loss of proprioceptive (along with vibratory and light touch) sensation occurs with isolated injury of the bilateral dorsal columns. A classic example is tabes dorsalis, a form of tertiary neurosyphilis that causes damage to the dorsal columns and dorsal nerve roots. {{exhibit_4}}

Educational objective: Ischemia of the anterior two-thirds of the spinal cord can occur with disruption of the anterior spinal artery blood supply. The resulting anterior cord syndrome causes bilateral distal loss of pain, temperature, and crude touch sensation (from injury to the spinothalamic tracts) and paralysis (from injury to the lateral corticospinal tracts). {{exhibit_5}}

explanation.zh:
该患者的胸主动脉瘤修复术并发了脊髓前2/3的缺血性损伤。该区域由脊髓前动脉灌注，脊髓前动脉接受来自节段动脉（例如肋间动脉）的血液供应，这些节段动脉源自胸主动脉。该区域的循环中断通常会导致前脊髓综合征，其特征在于以下双侧束损伤和临床体征：

* 脊髓丘脑束 (STT)：病变以下1-2个节段的疼痛/温度（侧脊髓丘脑）和轻触觉（前脊髓丘脑）感觉丧失。
* 前角（下运动神经元）：病变水平的弛缓性麻痹和肌肉萎缩。
* 外侧皮质脊髓束 (CST)（上运动神经元）：病变水平以下的瘫痪。最初发生脊髓休克引起的弛缓性麻痹（即，所有远端脊髓功能的暂时性丧失），但上运动神经元体征（例如，痉挛、反射亢进）随后在数天到数周内出现。

正如该患者一样，后柱通常会幸免于难（由于来自后脊髓动脉的循环完整），从而保留病变水平以下的本体感觉、振动觉和轻触觉。{{exhibit_2}}

（选项B）由于STT和后柱的损伤，所有下肢感觉（STTs和后柱损伤）和运动功能（CSTs损伤）的完全丧失可能出现在完全性脊髓损伤中，如脊髓横断时。

（选项C和E）轻触觉或疼痛/温度感觉的孤立性缺陷只能分别发生于前或侧STT的孤立性损伤。由于脊髓前动脉也为STT周围的束（例如CSTs）供血，因此仅对前或侧STT的双侧损伤极其罕见。

（选项D）本体感觉和运动功能的减弱可能与后柱和CSTs的同时损伤有关。一个经典的病因是后柱和侧脊髓白质的亚急性联合变性，见于维生素B12缺乏症。{{exhibit_3}}

（选项F）选择性地丧失本体感觉（以及振动觉和轻触觉）感觉，见于双侧后柱的孤立性损伤。一个经典的例子是脊髓痨，这是一种三期神经梅毒，会导致后柱和背根损伤。{{exhibit_4}}

教育目标：脊髓前2/3的缺血可因脊髓前动脉供血中断而发生。由此产生的前脊髓综合征会导致双侧远端疼痛、温度和轻触觉感觉丧失（由脊髓丘脑束损伤引起）和瘫痪（由侧皮质脊髓束损伤引起）。{{exhibit_5}}
